In this article, President Donald J. Trump issues a proclamation declaring December 17th as Wright Brothers Day. The proclamation pays tribute to Orville and Wilbur Wright, the American pioneers who achieved powered flight in 1903. The Wright brothers, who were bicycle mechanics by trade, overcame obstacles and failures to excel in aviation. Their achievement led to the transformation of modern life, including the development of commercial aviation, the U.S. Air Force, and the connection of nations through air travel. The article also mentions the influence of the Wright brothers on other aviation visionaries, such as the Apollo 11 astronauts and Joe Sutter, the designer of the iconic 747 jetliner. The proclamation celebrates the Wright brothers' ongoing inspiration and contribution to the strength and success of the United States.